Read the blog for our top tips that will get you through the new regulations. 
 
</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-4e6c" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dkYRCH cfhJKO pf-24_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-dtDOqo lfZCLK"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-25_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-brSvTw iyWbaU pf-26_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-27_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-29_">1.	Set up a work area if you haven’t already</span></h3></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-brSvTw iyWbaU pf-30_"><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-ab1d6638--Untitled-design-7_450x.png?v=1601370215" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-ab1d6638--Untitled-design-7.png?v=1601370215 1536w" width="450" height="302" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="workspace at home" title="habits to start at home" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-jQrDum igoalK pf-31_"/></div></div></div><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-32_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-brSvTw iyWbaU pf-33_"><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-34_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-36_">As many of us continue to work from home, uncertain of when we will be back to normal. So, it’s very important to find a work area, perhaps even get a desk if you haven’t got one already. Doing this will give you space to focus, limit distractions and helps you get into the right frame of mind.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-37_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-39_">2.	Start your day earlier to get things done</span></h3><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-40_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-42_">Since we have a 10pm curfew, we now have less time in the to socialise or enjoy being out of the house till late. Start your day earlier than usual to give you more time. If someone who enjoys eating out, perhaps swap dinners for brunch so you have the rest of the day to enjoy being out.</span></p></div></div></div></div></div><div data-section-id="pf-dac3" data-pf-type="Section" class="sc-dkYRCH cfhJKO pf-43_"><div style="--cw:1170px" class="sc-dtDOqo lfZCLK"><div class="sc-ezbkAF A-dmbO pf-44_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:0px;--s-sm:15px" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-brSvTw iyWbaU pf-45_"><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-46_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-48_">3.	Schedule some me time</span></h3><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-49_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-51_">It’s easy to have an unbalanced work/social life <a href="https://www.cliphair.co.uk/blogs/hair-blog/top-9-tips-for-working-from-home-productively" target="_blank">when working from home</a> and if you found yourself working late often, then be sure to schedule some me time during your day. This can be ensuring you follow your skin care routine, reading a book or fitting in 20 minutes of exercise or meditation.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-52_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-54_">4.	Organise your day</span></h3></div></div><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-brSvTw iyWbaU pf-55_"><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-56_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-58_">As many of us continue to work from home, uncertain of when we will be back to normal. So, it’s very important to find a work area, perhaps even get a desk if you haven’t got one already. Doing this will give you space to focus, limit distractions and helps you get into the right frame of mind.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-59_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-61_">5.	Avoid oversleeping</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-3bab1d66--Untitled-design-6_450x.png?v=1601370195" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-3bab1d66--Untitled-design-6.png?v=1601370195 1536w" width="450" height="300" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="habits to start during lockdown" title="habits to get you through the lockdown" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-jQrDum igoalK pf-62_"/><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-63_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-65_">With the option of a lie-in due to not having to commute, it’s easy for us to begin waking up later and some of us may have even become accustomed to hitting the snooze button on the alarm. Falling asleep again after the time you intended to wake up risks you falling into deep sleep again, making it even more difficult to wake up a little bit later. Try using a sleep calculator that will tell you the best times to go bed and wake up revived at your chosen time.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-66_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-68_">6. Stay social</span></h3><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-69_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-71_">Our phones and being connected online can often distract us. In order to keep in touch with friends and family, set time aside where you socialise and keep you phone on Do Not Disturb the rest of the day when working. It’s best to schedule this in the evening when you can relax a little. Having a quick chat with a close person quickly put a smile on your face.<p></p>
 </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-72_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-74_">7. Get into the habit of writing things down</span></h3><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-1d663832--Untitled-design-9_450x.png?v=1601370244" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/0069/6470/7389/t/9/assets/pf-1d663832--Untitled-design-9.png?v=1601370244 1536w" width="450" height="300" sizes="(min-width: 1536px) 1536px, (min-width: 1024px) 1280px, (min-width: 640px) 768px, 320px" loading="lazy" alt="writing things down lockdown habits" title="new habits at home" data-pf-type="Image" class="sc-jQrDum igoalK pf-75_"/><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-76_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-78_">Writing things down is a good way to remember things but can also be a fantastic way to clear your thoughts or even plan your day or your future. Besides, you can also start into the habit of writing positive things down which will certainly help you have a positive mindset each day.</span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-79_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-81_">8.	Learn something new</span></h3><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-82_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-84_">Spend time to hone an old hobby or set aside some time each day to study, watch, and learn a new craft or hobby. Even 10-15 minutes will go a long way in helping you find something new you love, and the time will certainly pass by quicker when you’re learning new things or doing something you love to do. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-85_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-87_">9.	Get outside</span></h3><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-88_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-90_">We now have more freedom than previously when it comes to how much often and how long we can be out. It’s easy to enjoy the comfort of your house rather than outside (now that it’s cold), but it’s important to keep making sure you spend some time outide, whether you’re taking your dog for a walk or going on a short jog, getting outside in the fresh air will help set a positive and energized tone for your day. </span></p><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-hOGkXu eBgidd pf-91_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-93_">10.	Look after your hair</span></h3><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-94_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-96_">Although we are home and not seeing that many people in the outside world, how we look can still affect how we feel. Learn some new hairstyles, make sure you are treating your hair and hair extensions well. Having a good hair day always makes an impact on how we feel throughout the day. </span></p><p class="sc-eGPXGI dCeUID pf-97_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-gUQvok zBuIu pf-99_"><p></p>
